WEBVTT

00:04.554 --> 00:06.671
But David Cronenberg turned him down,

00:06.763 --> 00:09.281
and that's why he didn't
direct "Return of the Jedi."

00:09.588 --> 00:10.968
And finally, I'd like to talk

00:11.002 --> 00:13.125
to everyone about the word "funt,"

00:13.250 --> 00:15.450
which, technically, is not a swear word

00:15.493 --> 00:17.540
but it could be argued
that it's the combination

00:17.574 --> 00:19.901
of two red alert words here at Whitlock.

00:19.955 --> 00:25.392
So please join me as we Punt the Funt.

00:25.477 --> 00:28.820
All right, all right.
Start shutting up, everybody.

00:29.103 --> 00:30.987
I bring amazing news.

00:31.031 --> 00:33.598
Last night, everything changed,

00:33.930 --> 00:36.149
but don't take it from me,

00:36.193 --> 00:38.021
take it from...

00:38.064 --> 00:39.196
[LIQUID GURGLING]

00:39.239 --> 00:40.937
[RETCHES]

00:40.980 --> 00:43.156
[SIGHING]

00:43.200 --> 00:44.462
Mayonnaise!

00:44.506 --> 00:46.203
[STUDENTS GROANING]

00:46.246 --> 00:48.939
So that is 128 ounces of mayonnaise.

00:48.973 --> 00:50.048
It's a lot, right?

00:50.082 --> 00:51.704
Is this part of the mission
to get revenge

00:51.737 --> 00:53.739
on Anthony's mean karate teacher?

00:53.776 --> 00:56.822
No, we're gonna cut off
Master Kyle's ponytail,

00:56.866 --> 00:59.085
but someone had to have an epiphany.

00:59.129 --> 01:01.653
Yes, yes, I had an epiphany.

01:01.697 --> 01:02.743
I did.

01:02.777 --> 01:05.004
You see, Anthony and I
witnessed a beautiful,

01:05.048 --> 01:06.484
if perplexing, thing.

01:06.528 --> 01:08.138
Right next to Anthony's dojo

01:08.181 --> 01:11.097
is the home of an average
Toledo family, working class,

01:11.141 --> 01:13.970
and last night they were having
some sort of big family dinner.

01:14.013 --> 01:15.667
Everyone had gathered
in the living room,

01:15.711 --> 01:17.234
everyone was hugging and laughing

01:17.277 --> 01:18.583
and eating sandwiches with mayo,

01:18.627 --> 01:20.672
eating celery dipped in mayo.

01:20.716 --> 01:23.196
At one point, I saw a girl,

01:23.240 --> 01:24.633
a child, really,

01:24.676 --> 01:28.235
- eat an entire spoonful of just mayo.
- Ew.

01:28.269 --> 01:29.923
I've never seen anything like it

01:29.957 --> 01:32.960
and I realized that they have
something that I don't have.

01:35.121 --> 01:37.646
Happiness. Yeah.

01:37.689 --> 01:39.691
They work hard all day long

01:39.735 --> 01:41.998
and then they reward themselves
with simple things.

01:42.041 --> 01:45.088
In this case, white gold.

01:45.131 --> 01:46.611
Mm-hmm.

01:46.655 --> 01:49.832
So, this is my new philosophical thesis.

01:49.875 --> 01:52.008
I'm going to describe how the good,

01:52.051 --> 01:55.228
hardworking people of Toledo
have unlocked the key

01:55.272 --> 01:58.231
to happiness through simplicity.

01:58.275 --> 02:01.234
[DETERMINED MUSIC]

02:01.278 --> 02:02.540
♪

02:02.593 --> 02:04.769
I'm gonna write a new book, y'all!

02:04.803 --> 02:05.978
Cool.

02:06.029 --> 02:07.160
What do you say, Anthony?

02:07.197 --> 02:08.590
Hip-hip... Nope.

02:08.633 --> 02:10.679
Nope? He doesn't wanna...

02:10.722 --> 02:13.377
So you're just gonna give up on
your mission to get out of Toledo?

02:13.421 --> 02:14.596
No, no, no, no, no.

02:14.639 --> 02:16.336
I'm going to win the Hiyu Isu prize.

02:16.380 --> 02:18.338
It's a major philosophy award.

02:18.382 --> 02:20.558
So, I write the book, win the prize,

02:20.602 --> 02:22.386
job offers and money come pouring in,

02:22.430 --> 02:25.233
and then I get the heck out of Toledo.

02:25.267 --> 02:27.260
Boom!

02:27.304 --> 02:29.262
Oh, boy, I see a new kid over here.

02:29.306 --> 02:31.177
Yeah, let me catch you up to speed.

02:31.221 --> 02:32.972
So I'm not gonna teach you
anything in here, okay?

02:33.005 --> 02:34.790
If you keep your mouth shut,
you get an A.

02:34.833 --> 02:37.096
If you say anything to anybody,
you get an F.

02:37.140 --> 02:39.272
Welcome to A.P. Bio.

02:39.316 --> 02:40.535
I've been here the whole time.

02:40.578 --> 02:44.234
[SCOFFS] Okay, well, jeez, you know,

02:44.277 --> 02:46.236
talk!

02:46.279 --> 02:47.977
[RAMONES' "LISTEN TO MY HEART"]

02:48.020 --> 02:49.587
♪ One, two, three, four ♪

02:49.639 --> 02:51.945
♪ Next time, I'll listen to my heart ♪

02:51.981 --> 02:54.984
♪ Next time, well, I'll be smart ♪

02:55.104 --> 03:01.767
♪

03:01.822 --> 03:03.354
<font color="6d6d6d">Synced & corrected by</font> <font color="#f7f4f4">reggielist</font>
<font color="6d6d6d">www.addic7ed.com</font>

03:04.166 --> 03:06.691
- Excuse me, Mr. Griffin.
- What?

03:06.735 --> 03:08.606
I'm currently applying
to a number of colleges,

03:08.650 --> 03:10.478
including Harvard.

03:10.521 --> 03:11.794
I was wondering if you could write me

03:11.827 --> 03:13.611
a letter of recommendation?

03:13.655 --> 03:14.917
- Oh yeah, me too.
- I want one.

03:14.960 --> 03:16.360
Yeah, I'm gonna need one, big-time.

03:16.396 --> 03:18.398
My GPA is trash.

03:18.442 --> 03:20.531
Yeah, that... that...
That's a hard pass, guys.

03:20.575 --> 03:23.186
Hard pass, um, but I have been
doing some research

03:23.229 --> 03:25.144
on this Isu philosophy prize

03:25.188 --> 03:26.537
and guess what?

03:26.581 --> 03:29.801
It comes with an award
of 50 million yen!

03:29.845 --> 03:32.412
Actually,
that's only 500,000 US dollars.

03:32.456 --> 03:35.154
Marcus, go to the office.

03:35.198 --> 03:36.373
[SIGHING]

03:36.416 --> 03:39.115
[GROANING]

03:39.158 --> 03:40.769
Where were we? [CHUCKLING]

03:40.812 --> 03:43.249
Oh right! I'm going to be
a Japanese millionaire.

03:43.293 --> 03:46.644
Yeah, the only tricky part
is that the submissions

03:46.688 --> 03:49.386
for the 2019 award
are due in three days.

03:49.429 --> 03:50.963
Luckily, I learned
how to cram pretty well.

03:50.996 --> 03:54.304
While getting my PhD, but
I just need help with the...

03:54.347 --> 03:56.001
"immersing myself in Toledo" part.

03:56.045 --> 03:59.527
I could take you to the Toledo Zoo.
It's pretty sweet.

03:59.570 --> 04:01.659
They have animals, sure,

04:01.703 --> 04:04.923
but they also have, like, concerts.

04:04.967 --> 04:06.849
Okay, Victor, that's, like,
the third or fourth time

04:06.882 --> 04:08.274
you've invited me to the zoo.

04:08.318 --> 04:09.591
I don't want to go there with you.

04:09.624 --> 04:11.495
Not for a concert or any other reason.

04:11.539 --> 04:13.410
What I need right now

04:13.453 --> 04:14.683
is to get in the trenches
with these people,

04:14.716 --> 04:16.281
feel what they feel.

04:16.326 --> 04:18.415
You know, like Jane Goodall
living with the chimps.

04:18.458 --> 04:21.331
I need to experience real hardworking,

04:21.374 --> 04:23.159
regular, manual labor jobs.

04:23.202 --> 04:24.508
You know what I'm saying?

04:24.552 --> 04:26.205
My aunt owns a landscaping company.

04:26.249 --> 04:27.598
Landscape... yes!

04:27.642 --> 04:29.045
Yes, okay you're doing great by the way,

04:29.078 --> 04:30.558
really fitting in.

04:30.601 --> 04:32.309
My dad's looking for someone
to fill a shift

04:32.342 --> 04:33.648
at the butcher shop.

04:33.691 --> 04:34.920
All right, this is great. What else?

04:34.953 --> 04:36.346
You could be a biology teacher.

04:36.389 --> 04:37.826
That's a regular job.

04:37.869 --> 04:39.751
Yeah, okay, I'll start
teaching you guys biology.

04:39.784 --> 04:41.264
- Really?
- Just kidding.

04:41.307 --> 04:42.874
What else, guys? Shout 'em out!

04:42.918 --> 04:45.660
- My uncle runs a car repair.
- My dad does demolition.

04:45.703 --> 04:47.618
Good, good. What else?

04:47.662 --> 04:49.185
You're all set at the butcher shop.

04:49.228 --> 04:50.882
[CHUCKLING] Awesome!

04:50.926 --> 04:53.156
Today I'm a butcher, tomorrow
I'm a Japanese millionaire.

04:53.189 --> 04:54.712
You know what I'm gonna do?

04:54.756 --> 04:57.585
Buy one of those Japanese
talking toilets.

04:57.628 --> 04:59.325
See what that has to say.

04:59.369 --> 05:01.414
This thing is toast.

05:01.458 --> 05:03.199
Well, how much is a new one gonna cost?

05:03.242 --> 05:05.201
Well, a top of the line one
gonna run you 5,000.

05:05.244 --> 05:06.724
[SIGHING]

05:06.768 --> 05:08.301
Now, Helen, you know
you really got to service

05:08.334 --> 05:09.520
these things every three months.

05:09.553 --> 05:11.337
This thing is shot.

05:11.381 --> 05:13.296
See ya, wouldn't wanna be ya.

05:15.472 --> 05:17.006
I don't know how this could've happened.

05:17.039 --> 05:20.346
I even put Post-Its up on
my never-forgets board.

05:20.390 --> 05:21.521
[SIGHING]

05:21.565 --> 05:23.523
[DETERMINED MUSIC]

05:23.567 --> 05:26.439
Oh, no. Oh, crap!

05:26.483 --> 05:29.181
They fell behind the copier.

05:29.225 --> 05:31.880
Oops, "water plant."

05:33.700 --> 05:36.711
"Check out Louis C.K. show."
I still got to do that.

05:36.754 --> 05:38.626
Oh, my garage door code!

05:38.669 --> 05:41.280
Yeah, I can start driving aga...

05:41.324 --> 05:43.892
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

05:43.935 --> 05:47.156
Yeah, "schedule copier maintenance."

05:47.199 --> 05:48.766
Ralph, I'm so sorry.

05:48.810 --> 05:50.126
I can't believe I let
this happen to our only copier.

05:50.159 --> 05:52.291
Okay, it's not the end of the world.

05:52.335 --> 05:54.642
Yes, it is.

05:54.685 --> 05:57.688
The copier is also a scanner.

05:57.732 --> 06:00.909
They can't scan, Ralph.
They can't even scan!

06:00.952 --> 06:04.521
Okay, okay, this might be a
bigger problem than we thought.

06:04.564 --> 06:06.131
Let's keep it between us for now, okay?

06:06.175 --> 06:07.829
What are you doing here, Marcus?

06:07.872 --> 06:09.961
- I...
- Did you use the new "F" word?

06:10.005 --> 06:11.310
No.

06:11.354 --> 06:12.888
Why are you guys standing
in front of the copier?

06:12.921 --> 06:15.053
Okay, that's it, Marcus.
Take your stuff and go home.

06:15.097 --> 06:17.490
- But I didn't do...
- You heard the principal! Go!

06:17.534 --> 06:19.362
You are not welcome here!

06:21.016 --> 06:23.148
[SIGHING]

06:23.192 --> 06:24.846
[SIGHING] Oh, God.

06:24.889 --> 06:26.674
You guys, we should go out Friday night.

06:26.717 --> 06:27.805
What should be celebrate?

06:27.849 --> 06:29.720
Friday is the 20th, right?

06:29.764 --> 06:31.853
I feel like we can
definitely find something

06:31.896 --> 06:33.637
to celebrate on the 20th.

06:33.681 --> 06:36.248
Oh Michelle, you white-ass Rihanna,

06:36.292 --> 06:38.033
of course, the 20th!

06:38.076 --> 06:40.035
Did my white-ass jog your memory, oh-oh!

06:40.078 --> 06:42.515
I can't believe that you remembered.

06:42.559 --> 06:44.779
It's exactly one year ago to the day

06:44.822 --> 06:46.215
since I got bangs.

06:46.258 --> 06:48.304
- Oh, no, no.
- That was a full year ago?

06:48.347 --> 06:49.609
Yes!

06:49.653 --> 06:51.350
BOTH: Bangs birthday!

06:51.394 --> 06:53.744
[GIGGLING]

06:53.788 --> 06:55.006
Hey, Daddy.

06:55.050 --> 06:56.366
You remember my dad, right, boss?

06:56.399 --> 06:57.574
Yeah, yeah, of course.

06:57.617 --> 06:59.021
Uh, hey, Ron, how are you doing there?

06:59.054 --> 07:00.718
Very, very pumped to be here.
This is great.

07:00.751 --> 07:02.797
Hi, Jack.

07:02.840 --> 07:04.886
Oh, just gonna put it on the fist there.

07:04.929 --> 07:06.801
All right. [CHUCKLING]

07:06.844 --> 07:08.498
"Every butt love a rub."

07:08.541 --> 07:09.934
Ah, I love that. So simple.

07:09.978 --> 07:11.762
Thank you, it's word play.

07:11.806 --> 07:12.861
Come over to the meat grinder.

07:12.894 --> 07:14.156
Yeah, absolutely.

07:14.199 --> 07:15.984
Let's do some classic blue-collar work.

07:16.027 --> 07:17.550
I love it.

07:17.594 --> 07:18.856
Yeah?

07:18.900 --> 07:20.510
I'm gonna start you off making sausage

07:20.553 --> 07:21.826
- out of pork shoulder.
- Mmhmm?

07:21.859 --> 07:22.991
Basically, you cut hunks

07:23.034 --> 07:24.644
of this pork shoulder into chunks,

07:24.688 --> 07:26.037
then do the same with lamb,

07:26.081 --> 07:28.387
then grab a big gunk
and shove it in the grinder.

07:28.431 --> 07:29.693
Oh.

07:29.737 --> 07:30.966
It's gonna poop it out
of this hole, see.

07:30.999 --> 07:33.044
Then take a long strand
of pork intestine.

07:33.088 --> 07:35.177
Feed it onto the worm end
and tie it off.

07:35.220 --> 07:36.841
Got to tell you, Ron,
you're making me hungry.

07:36.874 --> 07:38.223
Sorry about that.

07:38.267 --> 07:40.530
Then you repeat the whole thing
until 5:00 p.m.,

07:40.573 --> 07:42.793
or as we call it, "beer o'clock."

07:42.837 --> 07:46.101
"Beer o'clock"?
Oh man, that... that's fantastic!

07:46.144 --> 07:47.504
But let's go ahead and get started

07:47.537 --> 07:48.930
with the blue-collar work

07:48.973 --> 07:50.812
'cause, um, I'm on a little bit
of a deadline here.

07:50.845 --> 07:53.021
[PUNK MUSIC]

07:53.064 --> 07:55.240
[YELLING]

07:55.284 --> 07:56.546
[WHIRRING, CLANGING]

07:56.589 --> 07:58.156
Just put your hands in there.

07:58.200 --> 07:59.462
No gloves, huh?

07:59.505 --> 08:01.507
[GRUNTING]

08:01.551 --> 08:03.771
Yeah, I'm seeing a lot
of rollie pollies under here.

08:03.814 --> 08:05.685
Are they... they gonna be okay?

08:05.729 --> 08:06.904
Do you suppose?

08:06.948 --> 08:09.515
[CLEARS THROAT] Or it doesn't matter?

08:09.559 --> 08:10.778
Yeah, doesn't matter.

08:10.821 --> 08:13.476
Hey, I was just curious, uh,

08:13.519 --> 08:15.913
are you guys mad at your wives?

08:15.957 --> 08:18.960
Nothing, huh? Okay, back to work.

08:19.003 --> 08:21.614
- No, no, no! Not that wall!
- This isn't the wall?

08:21.658 --> 08:24.269
Whee! [CHUCKLING]

08:24.313 --> 08:25.803
The hell am I looking for in here, man?

08:25.836 --> 08:27.229
It's a mess.

08:27.272 --> 08:28.588
I don't think there's
any fixing this thing.

08:28.621 --> 08:30.885
Taco.

08:30.928 --> 08:33.017
[SINGER VOCALIZING]

08:35.759 --> 08:38.806
I heard Mr. Griffin left Big
Kim's Tacos around 2:00 a.m.

08:38.849 --> 08:40.677
Wasn't he supposed to be writing?

08:40.720 --> 08:42.461
His deadline is in two days.

08:42.505 --> 08:45.334
[SIGHING] Our little guy's
all tuckered out.

08:47.205 --> 08:48.816
[CLOCK TICKING]

08:51.383 --> 08:52.732
Aww.

08:52.776 --> 08:56.519
Shh. Good night, sweet price.

08:56.562 --> 08:59.609
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

09:04.962 --> 09:07.269
[GROANING]

09:07.312 --> 09:08.803
Let's go ahead and get started,
shall we?

09:08.836 --> 09:10.272
[CLEARS THROAT]

09:10.315 --> 09:12.970
Last night, I made
some progress on the book.

09:13.014 --> 09:15.843
Okay, so there's four basic
categories of happiness

09:15.886 --> 09:17.637
that I'm going to want
to focus on, all right?

09:17.670 --> 09:20.630
One, work a job where you can
see the physical results

09:20.673 --> 09:22.458
of your labor at the end of each day.

09:22.501 --> 09:24.852
Two, make up mundane celebrations

09:24.895 --> 09:27.115
to distract you
from your inevitable death.

09:27.158 --> 09:30.814
Number three, ingest sugary,
fatty, and salty things

09:30.858 --> 09:32.729
that release endorphins in your brain.

09:32.772 --> 09:35.297
And four, partner with
a convenient person

09:35.340 --> 09:37.821
within a 20-mile radius to procreate

09:37.865 --> 09:40.258
and therefore feel as though
a memory of you will live on.

09:40.302 --> 09:42.173
Now, we've only got 48 hours left,

09:42.217 --> 09:44.480
and, uh, we're still working
on part one.

09:44.523 --> 09:47.135
So I'm gonna need you guys
to be my research team

09:47.178 --> 09:48.658
while I focus on the writing.

09:48.701 --> 09:51.487
I need real-life examples
to back up my theory.

09:51.530 --> 09:53.793
So, Marcus, you're gonna be
cleaning the grease trap

09:53.837 --> 09:56.753
at Big Kim's Tacos
from midnight to 3:00 a.m.

09:56.796 --> 09:58.886
- New girl, you like Jeeps?
- I'm not new.

09:58.929 --> 10:01.976
You ever wonder how they
attach their windshield wipers?

10:02.019 --> 10:03.325
Great!

10:03.368 --> 10:05.457
[PERCUSSIVE MUSIC]

10:05.501 --> 10:07.155
Oh, hey, Michelle.

10:07.198 --> 10:08.808
Are you here to make copies?

10:08.852 --> 10:11.550
No, just dropping off permission slips.

10:11.594 --> 10:14.075
[SIGHING] Thank you.

10:14.118 --> 10:15.859
Hey, it's your birthday Friday, huh?

10:15.903 --> 10:17.078
You got any plans?

10:18.688 --> 10:20.168
Why would I have any plans?

10:20.211 --> 10:23.040
You're the only one who cares
about people at this school!

10:23.084 --> 10:26.609
Everyone else just cares about bangs!

10:27.827 --> 10:29.525
In fact...

10:29.568 --> 10:32.180
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

10:32.223 --> 10:33.616
Oh, don't!

10:33.659 --> 10:35.183
[CLANGING] Oh, oh!

10:35.226 --> 10:37.359
[PANTING]

10:37.402 --> 10:39.361
Oh! Oh, my gosh.

10:39.404 --> 10:41.276
That scared the candy out of me.

10:41.319 --> 10:42.712
But hey,

10:42.755 --> 10:46.194
more hair for my "locks of love" drive.

10:46.237 --> 10:49.197
And that's my lunch. Okay.

10:49.240 --> 10:50.894
[SCOFFING]

10:50.938 --> 10:55.029
Hair on the right, lunch on the left.

10:55.072 --> 10:57.335
Hey, Ralph, great news.

10:57.379 --> 10:58.554
I ordered the new copier.

10:58.597 --> 11:00.077
Not as great of news,

11:00.121 --> 11:01.687
it's gonna take ten days to get here.

11:01.731 --> 11:03.559
Okay, I'll tell you
what we're not gonna do.

11:03.602 --> 11:05.484
We're not gonna not get out
in front of this thing.

11:05.517 --> 11:10.218
In fact, we are going to get
in front of this.

11:10.261 --> 11:11.959
I mean, it's something
until cancer hits.

11:12.002 --> 11:13.569
Attention, Whitlock,

11:13.612 --> 11:15.484
this is your principal,
Principal Durbin.

11:15.527 --> 11:18.704
Uh, I just wanted to talk
to you about our copier,

11:18.748 --> 11:20.445
which is, uh, doing amazing.

11:20.489 --> 11:23.013
In fact, uh, better than ever,
if you ask me.

11:23.057 --> 11:26.234
But, uh, maybe we should also
be asking ourselves,

11:26.277 --> 11:29.237
why are we making so many copies?

11:29.280 --> 11:30.412
[FEEDBACK WHINES] Uh...

11:30.455 --> 11:31.510
That's a great idea, Ralph!

11:31.543 --> 11:33.371
Thanks, Helen.

11:33.415 --> 11:34.818
Long story short, everything's normal.

11:34.851 --> 11:37.071
Everyone have a Ram-tastic day,

11:37.114 --> 11:41.597
and, uh, less copying,
more original-ing.

11:41.640 --> 11:42.990
[FEEDBACK WHINES]

11:43.033 --> 11:44.078
[BOTH SIGHING]

11:44.121 --> 11:45.470
That's good.

11:45.514 --> 11:46.776
That's gonna buy us some time.

11:46.819 --> 11:48.212
- You're good at this.
- All right.

11:48.256 --> 11:49.866
Okay, thanks, here we...

11:49.909 --> 11:51.824
- I'm... I'm fist-bumping.
- Catch it?

11:51.868 --> 11:53.522
- No, you make a fist.
- All right.

11:53.565 --> 11:55.045
- And boop!
- Oh!

11:55.089 --> 11:56.612
[SCHOOL BELL RINGING]

11:56.655 --> 11:59.745
[FOREBODING MUSIC]

11:59.789 --> 12:00.964
♪

12:01.008 --> 12:03.793
Oh, great. Yeah. No, this is fantastic.

12:03.836 --> 12:05.414
What else did you learn
working your job?

12:05.447 --> 12:06.970
At that point, I was so tired,

12:07.014 --> 12:10.147
I accidentally glued my hand
to one of the carpet samples.

12:10.191 --> 12:11.627
Ouch. [CHUCKLES]

12:11.670 --> 12:12.987
You know, I do think
with a lot of these jobs,

12:13.020 --> 12:14.673
the more there's a threat of danger,

12:14.717 --> 12:16.849
the more meaningful
beer o'clock becomes.

12:16.893 --> 12:18.721
Yeah, did anyone else
encounter this, uh,

12:18.764 --> 12:21.115
beer o'clock phenomenon?

12:21.158 --> 12:22.290
Interesting.

12:22.333 --> 12:24.814
Uh, okay, who's next?

12:24.857 --> 12:26.337
Eduardo, go.

12:26.381 --> 12:29.688
I observed a construction
crew at Lagrange and Masters.

12:29.732 --> 12:31.821
At approximately 5:15 a.m.,

12:31.864 --> 12:33.692
a woman jogged past with her dog.

12:33.736 --> 12:35.346
I believe it was a Border Collie.

12:35.390 --> 12:39.002
One of the men exclaimed,
"Whoa, perfect ten!"

12:39.046 --> 12:41.526
I soon realized he was
referring to the woman,

12:41.570 --> 12:43.224
not the beautiful Collie.

12:43.267 --> 12:47.315
I asked around and apparently
this scale only goes to ten.

12:47.358 --> 12:49.360
So she had achieved the top score.

12:49.404 --> 12:51.623
Mm-hmm. Great work, Eduardo.

12:51.667 --> 12:53.103
That's sexual harassment.

12:53.147 --> 12:54.452
This whole thing is crazy.

12:54.496 --> 12:55.845
Kids are getting hurt.

12:55.888 --> 12:57.673
You're putting us in weird situations.

12:57.716 --> 12:59.022
We're not even getting

12:59.066 --> 13:00.512
our recommended eight hours of sleep.

13:00.545 --> 13:01.677
[SCHOOL BELL RINGING]

13:01.720 --> 13:03.113
All right, great work, guys.

13:03.157 --> 13:04.734
Keep it up, and, you know,
push through the pain.

13:04.767 --> 13:06.203
Don't even worry about it.

13:06.247 --> 13:07.954
Keep your eyes peeled
for more beer o'clocks.

13:07.987 --> 13:09.627
Hey, we're writing
a book, y'all! [LAUGHS]

13:13.689 --> 13:16.126
[SEEDY MUSIC]

13:16.170 --> 13:18.085
Oh, these are so cute!

13:18.128 --> 13:19.618
Right? I had my students
make them and put them

13:19.651 --> 13:21.958
in every teacher's desk.

13:22.001 --> 13:23.525
The chill ones, at least.

13:25.440 --> 13:28.573
Hey, guys. Guess who got bangs?

13:28.617 --> 13:30.097
[CHUCKLING] I did!

13:30.140 --> 13:31.881
So we can celebrate my bangs too!

13:31.924 --> 13:33.491
What's going on with you guys?

13:36.146 --> 13:38.757
Michelle, please explain.

13:38.801 --> 13:40.281
Explain what?

13:40.324 --> 13:43.762
Okay, so if I'm being
100% raw with you right now,

13:43.806 --> 13:45.416
not cool, Michelle. Mmmm.

13:45.460 --> 13:47.244
If you would've gotten
your rad new haircut

13:47.288 --> 13:49.246
any other week,
it would've been different.

13:49.290 --> 13:52.119
But you had to steal Stef's day
with your bomb-ass,

13:52.162 --> 13:54.991
new rickety isthmus haircut.

13:55.034 --> 13:56.340
Mm-mm.

13:56.384 --> 14:00.301
Just think about your choices, please.

14:00.344 --> 14:02.868
- Wait...
- I'm hurt.

14:04.218 --> 14:07.830
Wait, you... [SIGHS]

14:07.873 --> 14:09.484
- Helen?
- Psst, Ralph, down here.

14:09.527 --> 14:11.268
This announcement thing backfired.

14:11.312 --> 14:13.052
Now everyone wants to make copies.

14:13.096 --> 14:16.186
[POUNDING, RATTLING]

14:16.230 --> 14:17.622
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

14:17.666 --> 14:19.668
We're not gonna be able
to wait ten days.

14:19.711 --> 14:21.191
What are we gonna do?

14:21.235 --> 14:23.019
Well, I found a fix, but it's a...

14:23.062 --> 14:25.152
It's a bit of a nuclear option.

14:25.195 --> 14:28.503
Cancel the other order,
this'll be quicker.

14:28.546 --> 14:31.984
"Used copier for sale. Contact...

14:32.028 --> 14:35.118
Principal Kling
at Pineberry Elementary."

14:35.162 --> 14:39.078
Oh, Ralph, please don't do this.

14:39.122 --> 14:41.472
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

14:41.516 --> 14:43.605
♪

14:43.648 --> 14:47.261
You know, I would not have won

14:47.304 --> 14:49.219
"Innovative Principal of the Year"

14:49.263 --> 14:53.963
if I had sold copiers
to every "Johnny Tie Too Long"

14:54.006 --> 14:57.184
that came wandering into the office.

14:57.227 --> 15:01.405
Listen, we are in a real jam.

15:01.449 --> 15:05.148
Okay, look, I'd be happy
to sell you the copier.

15:05.192 --> 15:06.541
Oh, great.

15:06.584 --> 15:08.412
Unfortunately, it's not up to me.

15:08.456 --> 15:11.589
- Kling, don't... don't...
- It's up to Mr. Doobles.

15:11.633 --> 15:13.156
[IN HIGH-PITCHED VOICE] Hello!

15:13.200 --> 15:14.592
[CHUCKLING]

15:14.636 --> 15:17.552
I think that you should sell
them the copier.

15:17.595 --> 15:18.857
If...

15:18.901 --> 15:20.163
Don't.

15:20.207 --> 15:23.688
They kiss each other.

15:23.732 --> 15:25.037
Come on!

15:25.081 --> 15:26.223
It's the same thing every time!

15:26.256 --> 15:27.301
On the mouth!

15:27.344 --> 15:29.259
[WHISPERING] Sorry.

15:29.303 --> 15:31.827
[IN HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]
Do it, do it, do it!

15:31.870 --> 15:33.307
Mmm! Mmm!

15:33.350 --> 15:35.439
Ralph, let's just do it.

15:35.483 --> 15:37.659
- Yes, yes.
- Get up. Come on.

15:37.702 --> 15:39.487
Hey, what... what...

15:39.530 --> 15:41.706
You either take this check
and sell us that copier

15:41.750 --> 15:44.448
or I am gonna cut this
puppet's head off right now!

15:44.492 --> 15:46.145
- Mr. Doodles! Clear off!
- No!

15:46.189 --> 15:48.235
Wait, wait, Helen! You're hurting me!

15:48.278 --> 15:50.062
Well, you're hurting us!

15:50.106 --> 15:51.716
Okay, okay. Fine.

15:51.760 --> 15:53.631
You can have the copier.

15:55.285 --> 15:57.548
I need more material,
I need more details.

15:57.592 --> 15:59.289
Okay, I need you guys to get more jobs.

15:59.333 --> 16:00.562
That's what I need,
'cause I need more stuff here.

16:00.595 --> 16:01.954
Anthony, what's your evening like?

16:01.987 --> 16:04.251
Bruh, don't even.

16:04.294 --> 16:05.513
- [SCOFFS]
- Mr. Griffin.

16:05.556 --> 16:06.829
I have not slept or done any homework

16:06.862 --> 16:07.863
for the last two days.

16:07.906 --> 16:09.299
We're doing all this

16:09.343 --> 16:10.789
and you won't even give me
a college recommendation.

16:10.822 --> 16:12.259
I'm done!

16:12.302 --> 16:14.173
Okay, Sarika, well, that's...
We'll be fine!

16:14.217 --> 16:15.508
So, well... [DOOR CLICKS SHUT]

16:15.542 --> 16:16.605
I'm out too.

16:16.698 --> 16:17.742
Good-bye, Mr. Griffin.

16:17.786 --> 16:19.091
Oh, no, is Marcus...

16:19.135 --> 16:20.528
I can't do it without you, Marcus.

16:20.571 --> 16:22.312
Please, don't leave.
What do I have to do?

16:22.356 --> 16:23.705
Yeah, I'm done too.

16:23.748 --> 16:26.098
No Master Kyle's ponytail, no Anthony.

16:26.142 --> 16:27.415
Wait a second, Anthony.
Hold on, don't...

16:27.448 --> 16:28.492
I-I actually need you.

16:28.536 --> 16:29.591
Wait, don't... don't... don't...

16:29.624 --> 16:31.321
What about my deadline, dude?

16:31.365 --> 16:32.420
You guys are killing my book!

16:32.453 --> 16:33.932
No, you can't all go!

16:33.976 --> 16:35.064
Victor, stay. Come on.

16:35.107 --> 16:36.108
Bud, I need you.

16:36.152 --> 16:37.893
Sorry.

16:37.936 --> 16:39.764
[SCOFFS]

16:39.808 --> 16:41.331
There's my girl.

16:41.375 --> 16:43.246
Yeah, Heather's still on my side.

16:43.290 --> 16:45.335
Actually, I'm out too, boss.

16:45.379 --> 16:47.163
Oh... oh, my God.

16:47.206 --> 16:48.773
Heather, are you okay?

16:48.817 --> 16:50.340
Oh, it's just a rash.

16:50.384 --> 16:52.396
I think I'm allergic to
the lead at the smelting plant.

16:52.429 --> 16:54.823
I may need a little R&R, my dawg.

16:54.866 --> 16:57.173
- Oh.
- See ya.

16:57.216 --> 16:59.871
[COUGHING]

17:02.221 --> 17:04.310
[SIGHS] Funt.

17:04.354 --> 17:06.487
[DETERMINED MUSIC]

17:11.752 --> 17:13.015
♪

17:13.058 --> 17:14.799
[KEYS CLACKING]

17:16.584 --> 17:18.454
[SIGHS]

17:18.499 --> 17:24.940
♪

17:26.897 --> 17:29.031
[WHIRRING, BEEPING]

17:29.074 --> 17:31.120
See ya, wouldn't want to be ya.

17:31.163 --> 17:33.035
- [CHUCKLING] We did it!
- We did.

17:33.078 --> 17:35.907
Oh, God. [WHISTLES]

17:35.951 --> 17:37.300
Ralph, I need to say something

17:37.344 --> 17:39.824
so there won't be
any awkwardness between us.

17:39.868 --> 17:41.478
Okay.

17:41.522 --> 17:43.578
I didn't avoid kissing you
in Principal Kling's office

17:43.611 --> 17:45.352
because I think you're unattractive.

17:45.395 --> 17:47.223
Oh, that's not necessary.

17:47.266 --> 17:49.443
As you know, I like women.

17:50.269 --> 17:52.837
A lot. In that way.

17:52.881 --> 17:55.710
Like, but I do acknowledge
that you have a classic mouth.

17:55.753 --> 17:58.365
Hmm, this is going somewhere tricky.

17:58.408 --> 18:02.804
A juicy little mouth with
a long, long, doglike tongue.

18:02.847 --> 18:04.240
Hmm, woof. [CHUCKLING]

18:04.283 --> 18:05.894
And oh, I have noticed it,

18:05.937 --> 18:07.461
but I just wanted to talk this out

18:07.504 --> 18:10.420
so we didn't feel awkward or anything,

18:10.464 --> 18:11.900
and I feel so much better.

18:11.943 --> 18:14.555
Well, I'm... I'm glad
you... you feel better.

18:18.472 --> 18:21.300
Oh, Mary! Thank God. Hey, hi!

18:21.344 --> 18:23.085
Hey, guess what?

18:23.128 --> 18:25.609
I'd smooth Durbin if I wasn't
as gay as a tree full of birds.

18:25.653 --> 18:27.655
Yeah, I mean, I guess I'd kiss Durbin.

18:27.698 --> 18:30.092
Get some of that crazy dog tongue.

18:30.135 --> 18:31.398
[SNICKERING]

18:31.441 --> 18:32.921
See, I don't think I have that.

18:32.964 --> 18:35.445
Hey, will you tell Michelle
"Happy Birthday" for me?

18:35.489 --> 18:37.142
I'm not gonna make it tonight.

18:37.186 --> 18:40.450
I got reservations for the movies.

18:40.494 --> 18:42.452
Oh, I got a present for her too.

18:42.495 --> 18:43.570
Hold on.

18:43.612 --> 18:45.629
The 20th. Oh, damn.

18:45.673 --> 18:48.197
Here's my gift. Do you mind
giving Michelle this?

18:48.240 --> 18:50.112
Oh, go... go straight. Go straight.

18:50.155 --> 18:51.243
Whoa! God, this thing is...

18:51.287 --> 18:52.593
Oh, what the heck?

18:52.636 --> 18:55.204
- Oh!
- Mary, take the canoe!

18:55.247 --> 18:56.771
[SCHOOL BELL RINGING]

18:56.814 --> 19:01.166
Oh. He probably wants us
to proof his dumb book.

19:01.210 --> 19:03.299
Nope.

19:03.342 --> 19:05.162
These are college recommendations.

19:05.255 --> 19:06.302
They're what?

19:06.345 --> 19:07.782
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

19:07.825 --> 19:10.785
All right, start to shut up, everybody.

19:10.828 --> 19:13.962
Thanks for these letters, Mr. G.

19:14.005 --> 19:15.224
These are all so nice.

19:15.267 --> 19:16.791
Yeah, I said shut up.

19:16.834 --> 19:19.141
You think I'm a curious specimen?

19:19.184 --> 19:20.621
Yeah.

19:20.664 --> 19:23.493
My just says, "Old soul, nonsmoker."

19:23.537 --> 19:25.539
Yeah, it was starting to get late.

19:25.582 --> 19:28.019
You think I'm formidable?

19:28.063 --> 19:30.457
♪

19:30.500 --> 19:32.633
I didn't get an envelope.

19:32.676 --> 19:34.156
Oh, yeah?

19:34.199 --> 19:35.940
[PAPER CRINKLING]

19:39.335 --> 19:40.815
[GASPING]

19:40.858 --> 19:43.165
Master Kyle's ponytail!

19:43.208 --> 19:45.428
[CHALK SCRAPING]

19:45.472 --> 19:46.821
Are you okay, boss?

19:46.864 --> 19:48.605
Well, yeah, you know,

19:48.649 --> 19:50.520
Master Kyle did eventually
let his guard down

19:50.564 --> 19:52.087
during his breakfast at Denny's,

19:52.130 --> 19:53.697
but, uh, Anthony failed to mention

19:53.741 --> 19:56.744
that Mrs. Master Kyle
was also a black belt.

19:56.787 --> 19:58.006
Yeah.

19:58.049 --> 19:59.529
Yeah.

19:59.573 --> 20:01.618
These letters must've
taken you all night.

20:01.662 --> 20:03.881
What about your deadline?

20:03.925 --> 20:05.622
I missed it.

20:05.666 --> 20:07.363
- Aww.
- It's okay, it's all right.

20:07.406 --> 20:08.853
All right, shut up,
shut up, shut up. It's fine.

20:08.886 --> 20:10.376
It's given me a little bit more
time to, uh,

20:10.409 --> 20:12.411
personally collect more examples of, uh,

20:12.455 --> 20:15.371
authentic day-to-day Toledo happiness.

20:15.414 --> 20:17.547
Yeah, before Germany's Schweizer award,

20:17.591 --> 20:18.940
which is another big award.

20:18.983 --> 20:20.419
What is this?

20:20.463 --> 20:23.684
I just need to keep observing
real Toledoans

20:23.727 --> 20:26.338
in their natural... element.

20:26.382 --> 20:28.166
Party at Wesley's for
Stef's Bangs Birthday?

20:28.210 --> 20:29.472
Oh.

20:29.516 --> 20:31.648
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

20:31.692 --> 20:32.997
[LAUGHING]

20:33.041 --> 20:35.347
- Yay, to Stef's bangs.
- Yes, to my bangs!

20:35.391 --> 20:36.871
Absolutely, to your hair.

20:36.914 --> 20:38.437
- Oh.
- Mmm.

20:38.481 --> 20:42.137
Oh, I should've mixed it
with some fruit juice.

20:42.180 --> 20:44.182
There she is, our birthday girl!

20:44.226 --> 20:45.444
Happy birthday, Michelle!

20:45.488 --> 20:46.881
[CHEERING]

20:46.924 --> 20:48.709
Did you think we forgot
about your birthday?

20:48.752 --> 20:51.712
"Happy birthday to Stef's...
Our bangsing friend, Mich."

20:51.755 --> 20:55.716
You guys! You jammed fries into
Stef's bangs cake for me?

20:55.759 --> 20:57.587
Yes, girl, we love you,

20:57.631 --> 21:01.286
and your birthday is way more
important than some haircut.

21:01.330 --> 21:04.072
Thank you so much. I love you guys.

21:04.115 --> 21:07.989
Hey, um, is this some type
of aioli sauce or something?

21:08.032 --> 21:09.251
'Cause it's delicious.

21:09.294 --> 21:12.123
It's just mayonnaise.

21:12.167 --> 21:16.084
[CHEERFUL MUSIC]

21:16.127 --> 21:17.912
White gold.

21:17.955 --> 21:19.609
♪
